  "shortBio": "Known as the “Shelfward Sentinel of Gritlanes,” Pebblit belongs to Stoneheart Canyon’s living edges. Pebblits move mineral-plated and deliberate, stay calm with strangers, and lean on stone shell when the air turns strange. They savor Stonefruit. In Stoneheart Canyon, they favor Stonefruit and teach quieter routes to those who listen.",
  "standardBio": "Pebblit, titled among keepers as “Shelfward Sentinel,” carries quiet loyalty in every movement. Native to Stoneheart Canyon, the species endures through dust and canyon grit, leaving traces that other Riftlings can follow like soft maps. Wild groups form loose bonds rather than rigid packs; a calm individual may become the emotional center of a small hearthline. They eat Stonefruit eagerly and dislike food that smells of neglect or spoilage. Ancient keepers carved Pebblit silhouettes into travel stones, believing the species guided the lost. Modern hatcheries record them as reliable companions; their emotional intelligence above tool craft makes training feel like conversation. Their signature ability, Pebble Roll, reflects a life shaped by Stoneheart Canyon more than by arena ambition. Their quiet is mistaken for emptiness. In truth they are listening harder than louder species. Young Pebblits practice Pebble Roll as play long before they understand battle. Adults teach by demonstration: where to rest, what to avoid, how to share warmth or shade.",
  "fullLore": "Pebblits first condensed from residual fossilhum along the living edges of Stoneheart Canyon after early Rift fractures cooled into weather. Their eggs appear where dust and canyon grit gathers into stillness—never in the loudest danger, always in the pocket of calm beside it. Early surveyors mistook them for ambient phenomena until a Pebblit returned a dropped lantern, carefully, as if returning a promise.\n\nIn ancient eras, regional peoples treated Pebblits as omen-bearers rather than pets. Carvings show them walking ahead of caravans, pausing at unstable ground, and curling around children during ashfall or fog. The species was never “tamed” in the old sense; it chose. That choice culture survives in modern Riftkeeper etiquette: you do not yank a Pebblit into a bond. You invite, wait, and keep the invitation honest.\n\nModern history is quieter and more practical. Hatcheries map Pebblit care cycles with the same seriousness given to rare lines, because common does not mean shallow. Stoneheart Canyon still holds wild populations that trade soft greetings with passerby pets. After major Rift events, Pebblits often appear first at recovery centers—not as heroes, but as inventory clerks of comfort, counting who is cold, hungry, or afraid.\n\nNatural behavior is calm at the core and adaptable at the edges. They are mineral-plated and deliberate, companion-sized, easy to cradle, and communicate through tap-codes on stone or wood. Socially, they prefer small trusted circles; strangers are assessed by scent, posture, and whether a keeper’s voice stays kind under stress. Intelligence presents as emotional intelligence above tool craft. They sleep in elevated shelves and prefer weather that matches their affinity’s comfort band.\n\nEcologically, Pebblits act as cleanup foragers within Stoneheart Canyon. Allies often include Stonegrub and Crystowl; rivalries with Tidewisp and Moonray are usually about nesting space or shiny refuse, not blood feuds. Predators are rare—most threats come from collapsing terrain and careless machines rather than jaws.\n\nCulture around them is affectionate and slightly superstitious. Festival stories say the first Riftkeepers learned patience by watching Pebblits wait out weather rather than fight it. Collectors prize unusual cosmetics, yet marketplace notes remind buyers that verified care history matters more than glitter. The common misunderstanding remains: Their quiet is mistaken for emptiness. In truth they are listening harder than louder species. The hidden truth keepers debate in soft rooms is simpler and stranger: Pebblits can hear micro-fractures in Riftstone as a pressure change behind the ears.\n\nFrom egg to evolved form, their life story stays continuous. Eggs look like soft lantern pods veined with stone light. Hatchlings are clumsy with sincerity; adults become specialists of place; evolved stages sharpen instinct without erasing childhood habits. Battle tendencies favor protective bursts, and evolution philosophy insists transformation should answer lived experience—not fashion.\n\nFor Riftkeepers, a Pebblit is a living chapter of Stoneheart Canyon. Feed it Stonefruit, respect its calm tempo, and it will teach you the region’s quieter grammar: which winds lie, which stones remember, which silences are safe. Personal quests often begin with a shell symbol, a remembered scent, or a dream of a door that only opens when the bond is honest. That is the Pebblit bargain—not destiny sold at rarity price, but a life that continues because you showed up.",
